1. Create New Application - cmd> ionic start myApp blank --type=ionic-angular
2. Build App cmd - ionic build
3. Add android to the project - cmd> npx cap add android
4. Open Project in Android Studio cmd> npx cap open android
5. Create icon using any image editor size should be 1024 X 1024 for icon
6. android Studio select app > res right click then select new > image asset 
7. Configure Image Asset Dialog
Select Asset Type = image and set path to where you saved your icon image - Talk about the other options for formating the icon
8. Preview window. If you need to scale please do so by using the trim option.
9. Start your Android emulator to preview the icon 



live reload purposes
ionic capacitor run android --livereload --external